#    Types of Attacks Performed by Malicious Extensions:- 
#         1.  Information Stealing (Infostealers
#         2.  Adware and Malvertising
#         3.  Phishing and Social Engineering
#         4.  Man-in-the-Browser (MitB) Attacks  
#         5.  Malware Delivery and Installation
#         6.  Denial of Service (DoS) / Distributed DoS (DDoS)
#         7.  Supply Chain Attacks
#         8.  Trojan/virus Attacks

___________________________________________________________________

#     Preventing malicious browser extensions 
#           1. Scrutinize Permissions Before Installation
#           2. Keep Your Browser and Extensions Updated
#           3. Use Strong Antivirus/Anti-Malware Software
#           4. Clear Browser Cache and Cookies Regularly
#           5. Continuous Monitoring and Auditing
#           6. Implement Extension Allowlisting/Denylisting (Whitelisting/Blacklisting)
